> Presumably they do that for a reason.

Perhaps the BBS quote above makes sense in context of their paper
(I, unfortunately, do not have a copy to refer to), but it makes
little sense by itself.  BBS does rely on the unproven assumption
that factoring is hard.


> The whole point of a BB&S generator is to have provable strength,
> because the generator itself is slow.

